fields.description: The height of the output video for this layer. The value can be absolute (in pixels) or relative (in percentage). For example 50% means the output video has half as many pixels in height as the input.
fields.name: Height

fields.description: The alphanumeric label for this layer, which can be used in multiplexing different video and audio layers, or in naming the output file.
fields.name: Label

fields.description: The compression quality of the JPEG output. Range is from 0-100 and the default is 70.
fields.name: Quality

fields.description: The width of the output video for this layer. The value can be absolute (in pixels) or relative (in percentage). For example 50% means the output video has half as many pixels in width as the input.
fields.name: Width
